		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yup, the Rodney Zakks book, 4th edition. 
<br />
<br />I've read that there were some errors and confusion in the previous editions, but the 4th ed. is good.
<br />
<br />Another good one I just received is "6502 Software Design" by Leo Scanlon.
<br />
<br />"Atari Roots" by Mark Andrews is a very good book for us beginners.
<br />
<br />What are you reading?

		

		</td>
